        "baseOption": {
          "name": "—",
          "label": "Bard — Base / No Subclass",
          "includedInSubclassDescriptions": false
        },
        "description": "Bards are versatile artists, speakers, historians, spies, duelists, diplomats, and magical performers whose power comes through story, rhythm, inspiration, and social awareness. They are rarely limited to one battlefield role: a bard can heal, hinder, charm, scout, negotiate, blast, or support depending on their chosen college and spell selection. Their defining strength is adaptability, especially in campaigns that reward skill use, roleplay, improvisation, and problem solving outside of simple combat. A bard may be a court poet, revolutionary singer, traveling comedian, scholar of lost epics, battlefield drummer, spirit medium, silver-tongued envoy, or blade-dancer whose performance is also a weapon. Mechanically, they lean on Charisma, skills, Bardic Inspiration, and flexible spellcasting. Narratively, bards remind the table that culture is power: names, songs, rumors, speeches, and memories can change kingdoms as surely as swords. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
