        "description": "Clerics are divine spellcasters who channel sacred power through faith, service, philosophy, cosmic allegiance, or a personal relationship with a godlike force. They are not simply healers; they can become armored front-line champions, radiant destroyers, battlefield commanders, scholars, exorcists, peacemakers, storm-callers, grave wardens, or trickster-priests depending on their domain. In a party, clerics often provide durability, restoration, protection, utility, and decisive magic against undead or supernatural threats. Their stories can involve temples, pilgrimages, heresies, vows, miracles, doubt, holy politics, and the burden of representing a power larger than themselves. Mechanically, they rely on Wisdom, prepared spells, domain features, and strong support options. A cleric’s subclass is especially identity-defining because the domain explains what kind of divinity or sacred principle answers when the character prays. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
