        "description": "Druids are primal spellcasters who draw power from nature, spirits, cycles, stars, elemental forces, beasts, fungi, wildfire, dreams, and the living balance of the world. They can heal, control terrain, summon allies, transform, gather information, and punish those who damage the natural order. In a party, druids often fill flexible support, control, exploration, and survival roles, with some circles becoming powerful front-line shapeshifters or specialist casters. Their stories may center on sacred groves, old pacts, ecological collapse, borderlands between civilization and wilderness, seasonal rites, or the moral complexity of nature itself. Mechanically, they lean on Wisdom, prepared spells, Wild Shape, and concentration. Narratively, druids work best when nature is more than scenery: it is an active community of beasts, plants, spirits, storms, memories, and consequences. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
