        "description": "Fighters are weapon masters whose strength comes from training, discipline, adaptability, and sheer practical competence. They can be soldiers, duelists, knights, archers, bodyguards, gladiators, tacticians, magical warriors, psychic combatants, rune-carved giantslayers, or champions of a martial order. In a party, fighters usually provide reliable damage, strong defenses, battlefield presence, and consistency across long adventuring days. Unlike classes defined by one supernatural source, the fighter’s identity is shaped by method: how they fight, why they trained, what code they follow, and what they do when skill is not enough. Mechanically, fighters support many builds because they gain strong weapon and armor options, repeated attacks, and flexible ability-score growth. Their subclasses can remain grounded or become highly magical, making the class useful for both realistic martial heroes and mythic battlefield specialists. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
