        "description": "Paladins are sacred warriors whose magic is bound to an oath, ideal, vow, or moral obsession strong enough to reshape the world around them. They combine martial durability with divine force, healing, protection, and explosive smiting power. In a party, paladins often serve as front-line defenders, leaders, emergency healers, and moral anchors, though some oaths create darker conquerors, avengers, redeemers, or oathbreakers. A paladin’s story is rarely only about religion; it is about what promise they refuse to abandon and what cost they will pay to keep it. Mechanically, they lean on Strength or Dexterity, Charisma, armor, auras, spell slots, and decisive weapon strikes. Narratively, paladins are strongest when their oath creates real tension: mercy versus justice, glory versus humility, law versus compassion, vengeance versus peace, or vigilance versus paranoia. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
