        "baseOption": {
          "name": "—",
          "label": "Ranger — Base / No Subclass",
          "includedInSubclassDescriptions": false
        },
        "description": "Rangers are wandering hunters, scouts, survivalists, monster specialists, and primal warriors who stand between civilization and the dangerous edges of the world. They combine martial skill, exploration talent, nature magic, stealth, tracking, and specialized knowledge of threats. In a party, rangers often serve as scouts, strikers, guides, ambushers, and troubleshooters in wilderness or frontier campaigns, but many subclasses work well in cities, planes, ruins, and horror stories too. A ranger might be a border warden, dragon-bonded guardian, fey-touched diplomat, shadowy ambusher, planar traveler, swarm keeper, beast trainer, or monster slayer. Mechanically, they often rely on Dexterity or Strength, Wisdom, weapon attacks, mobility, and selected spells. Narratively, the ranger is defined by attention: they notice tracks, weather, habits, migrations, weaknesses, and the small signs that danger is already near. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
