        "baseOption": {
          "name": "—",
          "label": "Rogue — Base / No Subclass",
          "includedInSubclassDescriptions": false
        },
        "description": "Rogues are experts, infiltrators, scouts, duelists, assassins, investigators, thieves, manipulators, and problem solvers who win through precision rather than brute force. In a party, they often provide scouting, skill coverage, trap handling, social trickery, and high single-target damage through well-timed attacks. Rogues thrive in campaigns with secrets, locks, lies, patrols, mysteries, negotiations, and uneven terrain, but they can also shine in combat through mobility and careful positioning. A rogue may be a charming swashbuckler, haunted medium, psychic blade, mastermind, detective, wilderness scout, magical trickster, professional thief, or cold assassin. Mechanically, rogues lean on Dexterity, skills, expertise, cunning movement, and Sneak Attack. Narratively, the class is about leverage: the right word, the right disguise, the right angle, the right silence, and the exact moment when a hidden weakness becomes fatal. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
