        "baseOption": {
          "name": "—",
          "label": "Wizard — Base / No Subclass",
          "includedInSubclassDescriptions": false
        },
        "description": "Wizards are scholarly arcane spellcasters who master magic through study, experimentation, notation, theory, memory, and disciplined preparation. They are the classic researchers of spellcraft: fragile in body but immense in possibility when given time, information, and a full spellbook. In a party, wizards can become controllers, blasters, ritualists, utility casters, battlefield engineers, diviners, illusionists, necromancers, defensive specialists, or magical problem solvers. Their stories often involve academies, forbidden libraries, apprenticeships, rival scholars, dangerous inventions, lost languages, and the ethical cost of knowledge. Mechanically, wizards rely on Intelligence, prepared spells, rituals, and the broadest arcane toolbox. Their subclass usually represents a school, method, or theory of magic rather than a bloodline or patron, making each wizard feel like a practitioner who chose a lens through which to understand reality. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
