        "description": "Artificers are magical inventors who turn arcane theory into tools, armor, constructs, elixirs, weapons, and devices. They sit between spellcaster, engineer, alchemist, enchanter, and battlefield technician, making them ideal for characters who solve problems by building something clever. In a party, artificers often provide support, utility, item enhancement, defensive technology, healing, and flexible damage depending on their specialist path. Their stories fit laboratories, guilds, war workshops, ancient ruins, magewright colleges, clockwork temples, airships, prosthetic craft, and strange experiments. Mechanically, artificers rely on Intelligence, infusions, prepared spells, tool proficiencies, and subclass-built equipment. Narratively, they are excellent for worlds where magic has infrastructure: locks, engines, medical devices, arcane firearms, animated armor, living steel, and inventions that blur the line between spell and machine. In a generator, this class should influence combat role, voice posture, equipment, duties, common conflicts, and how an NPC reacts when danger interrupts ordinary life.",
